                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13944433" author="king821221" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 14:40:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If possible, I may help on this since I recently start looking into mahout. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944434" author="smarthi" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 14:42:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Go ahead and submit a patch when done.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944436" author="king821221" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 14:46:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When is the deadline?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944437" author="smarthi" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 14:55:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When ur patch is done &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944457" author="pferrel" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 16:10:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The install is svn only, why not add the git equivalent. Many users will be familiar with it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944460" author="ssc" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 16:19:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree. I think the first thing should be adding mahout as maven dependency to an existing java project, than downloading the prebuilt mahout and the last thing should be building from source.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the page it seems that people have to build mahout from source to play with it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944467" author="andrew.musselman" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 16:36:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree with Pat and Sebastian&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944474" author="andrew.musselman" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 16:50:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Probably should also note in the README that the pre-built version doesn&apos;t need to be built.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944487" author="pferrel" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 17:24:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I still like the command line tour. To really make it a quickstart, there is no build, no git or svn checkout, no POM editing, just download and run. This makes it accessible to anyone even if they aren&apos;t Java programmers. Most of my first uses were through bash scripts running the command line. With a tiny bit of Java to read the output (which we should probably find a way to remove). Shouldn&apos;t we try to reach web and mobile app devs? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The uses of Mahout are so much larger than its current audience.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944496" author="ssc" created="Sun, 23 Mar 2014 17:46:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe we should also add links to easy-to-use top level layers like &lt;a href=&quot;http://prediction.io&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://prediction.io&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/plista/kornakapi&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/plista/kornakapi&lt;/a&gt; ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13944973" author="king821221" created="Mon, 24 Mar 2014 12:40:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As for adding maven dependency of mahout, provide some explanations as what this link answers, could it be OK? &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9072223/how-to-add-maven-dependencies-for-mahout-and-hadoop&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9072223/how-to-add-maven-dependencies-for-mahout-and-hadoop&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13950577" author="king821221" created="Fri, 28 Mar 2014 10:59:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hi, would like to know how to verify the html document generated from the udpated mdtext generates correct html document? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954662" author="king821221" created="Sun, 30 Mar 2014 13:33:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Step 1: how to add Mahout as maven dependency in user&apos;s maven project&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954768" author="ssc" created="Sun, 30 Mar 2014 18:59:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Added your changes + some additions to &lt;a href=&quot;https://mahout.apache.org/users/basics/quickstart.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://mahout.apache.org/users/basics/quickstart.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should we add more or is this fine for a quickstart and we should focus on the examples? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954902" author="andrew.musselman" created="Mon, 31 Mar 2014 02:51:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking good; can we should elaborate on what examples are available on this page?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A lot of people come in and use the examples to find their way around, so a section devoted to examples would be helpful.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954908" author="king821221" created="Mon, 31 Mar 2014 03:04:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;My opinion is to elaborate on the examples for different algorithms since user&apos;s requirement is specific, for instance, they would like to do prediction or recommendation. So rich examples on how to use different algorithms may be more helpful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would like to listen to your ideas before moving on.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954910" author="king821221" created="Mon, 31 Mar 2014 03:08:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;As for the maven dependency, I find that there is some already existing descriptions on how to use Mahout in maven.&lt;a href=&quot;https://mahout.apache.org/general/downloads.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://mahout.apache.org/general/downloads.html&lt;/a&gt;. Should we move them to the quick start page or create a link in quick start to this page?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954912" author="andrew.musselman" created="Mon, 31 Mar 2014 03:09:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m talking specifically about the &quot;examples&quot; at this location &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/mahout/trunk/examples/bin&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/mahout/trunk/examples/bin&lt;/a&gt; which are currently the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;classify-20newsgroups.sh&lt;br/&gt;
cluster-reuters.sh&lt;br/&gt;
cluster-syntheticcontrol.sh&lt;br/&gt;
create-rf-data.sh&lt;br/&gt;
factorize-movielens-1M.sh&lt;br/&gt;
factorize-netflix.sh&lt;br/&gt;
lda.algorithm&lt;br/&gt;
run-rf.sh&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These bash scripts can be a good foothold into how to use the project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does that sound reasonable?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954916" author="king821221" created="Mon, 31 Mar 2014 03:17:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;OK.  Understand your idea.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe what I mean by &quot;example&quot; more talk about stuff such as &lt;a href=&quot;https://mahout.apache.org/users/recommender/userbased-5-minutes.html:&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://mahout.apache.org/users/recommender/userbased-5-minutes.html:&lt;/a&gt; how to use Mahout classes and interfaces in a java program.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954918" author="andrew.musselman" created="Mon, 31 Mar 2014 03:21:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, that looks like a good link to put on the quickstart page also.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954988" author="ssc" created="Mon, 31 Mar 2014 08:13:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the duplication of the maven snippets is fine. I wouldn&apos;t want to send the users to another page for that, as it might confuse them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree, that it would be great to have a more extensive list of examples, maybe one section describing the bash scripts and another linking to tutorials. Could you prepare that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=king821221&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;king821221&quot;&gt;jian wang&lt;/a&gt; ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13954991" author="king821221" created="Mon, 31 Mar 2014 08:15:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, I will do it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13961019" author="ssc" created="Sat, 5 Apr 2014 10:10:37 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Jian, thank you very much, I&apos;ve updated the website.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13961027" author="hudson" created="Sat, 5 Apr 2014 10:38:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in Mahout-Quality #2553 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/2553/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/2553/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1482&quot; title=&quot;Rework quickstart website&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-1482&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-1482&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Rework quickstart website (ssc: rev 1585027)&lt;/p&gt;
